      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC03aba460256810058980df0f9b3366d2"></a>Check of the camshafts and supports
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e13159"> </a>Check the cam contact surfaces for scratches, grooves, steps and waving.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e13161"> </a>Worn cams are frequently the cause of poor timing, which leads to loss of engine power.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e13163"> </a>Place the camshaft between two centres and check the runout on the areas indicated using two dial gauges.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e13165"> </a>Service limit: 0.1&nbsp;mm.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_016201938.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e13170"> </a>Visually inspect the camshaft tracks for scoring and abnormal wear. If any of the above defects are found, the camshaft should
            be renewed.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e13172"> </a>If you find scoring or excessive wear, check the operation of the engine lubrication circuit.
         </div>
      </div>
